labs around the United States

00:47:22.740 --> 00:47:27.450 align:middle line:84%
objects that are large enough
to be seen by the naked eye

00:47:27.450 --> 00:47:30.560 align:middle line:84%
and they are in two
places simultaneously.

00:47:30.560 --> 00:47:33.750 align:middle line:84%
You can actually take
a photograph of them.

00:47:33.750 --> 00:47:37.930 align:middle line:84%
Now, I suppose if you showed
a photograph, they'd say,

00:47:37.930 --> 00:47:40.910 align:middle line:84%
oh, great here's this
nice blob of colored light

00:47:40.910 --> 00:47:43.570 align:middle line:84%
and I see there's a bit of
it over here and a little bit

00:47:43.570 --> 00:47:44.370 align:middle line:90%
here.

00:47:44.370 --> 00:47:47.040 align:middle line:84%
So you got a picture of two
dots, what's the big deal?

00:47:47.040 --> 00:47:50.040 align:middle line:90%
Superposition is pre-detection.

00:47:50.040 --> 00:47:54.880 align:middle line:84%
What I was speaking about in
the film is post-detection.

00:47:54.880 --> 00:47:59.850 align:middle line:84%
Now, under normal
circumstances, a single object,

00:47:59.850 --> 00:48:05.040 align:middle line:84%
once it has been detected,
is in just one position.

00:48:05.040 --> 00:48:07.830 align:middle line:84%
However, there are
states of matter

00:48:07.830 --> 00:48:12.060 align:middle line:84%
that have been created
now in which objects

00:48:12.060 --> 00:48:15.120 align:middle line:84%
can be in multiple
positions simultaneously,

00:48:15.120 --> 00:48:21.810 align:middle line:84%
not just two, but actually
as many as 3,000 positions.

00:48:21.810 --> 00:48:25.610 align:middle line:84%
The first of these
objects were called

00:48:25.610 --> 00:48:28.400 align:middle line:90%
Bose-Einstein condensates.

00:48:28.400 --> 00:48:31.310 align:middle line:84%
And they are single
wave functions,

00:48:31.310 --> 00:48:34.810 align:middle line:84%
meaning they are
single particles.

00:48:34.810 --> 00:48:37.460 align:middle line:84%
But even though they're
a single wave function,

00:48:37.460 --> 00:48:40.967 align:middle line:84%
the wave function has
multiple positions.

00:48:40.967 --> 00:48:43.550 align:middle line:84%
And so we'll look, look, look,
right in the chamber, you know,

00:48:43.550 --> 00:48:44.390 align:middle line:90%
you can see it right there.

00:48:44.390 --> 00:48:45.530 align:middle line:90%
Oh, I see two things there.

00:48:45.530 --> 00:48:48.320 align:middle line:84%
No, no, no, that's not two
things, that's one thing.

00:48:48.320 --> 00:48:50.060 align:middle line:84%
It's the same thing
in two places.

00:48:50.060 --> 00:48:54.260 align:middle line:84%
The tricky point here is
that it's still a single wave

00:48:54.260 --> 00:48:55.440 align:middle line:90%
function.

00:48:55.440 --> 00:49:00.730 align:middle line:84%
It's not 3,000 separate
wave functions,

00:49:00.730 --> 00:49:03.590 align:middle line:90%
it's one wave function.

00:49:03.590 --> 00:49:05.015 align:middle line:90%
So it's one particle.

00:49:05.015 --> 00:49:08.790 align:middle line:90%


00:49:08.790 --> 00:49:11.410 align:middle line:84%
I'm not sure that
people's jaw would

00:49:11.410 --> 00:49:17.380 align:middle line:84%
drop about it because I don't
think people really believe it.

00:49:17.380 --> 00:49:19.620 align:middle line:84%
I don't mean that people
say, oh, you're lying

00:49:19.620 --> 00:49:21.420 align:middle line:84%
or, oh, the scientists
are confused,

00:49:21.420 --> 00:49:24.480 align:middle line:84%
I think it is so mysterious
that you can't even

00:49:24.480 --> 00:49:26.670 align:middle line:90%
understand how amazing it is.

00:49:26.670 --> 00:49:32.102 align:middle line:84%
One particle in 3,000
different locations.

00:49:32.102 --> 00:49:33.810 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, if you were
to weigh one of them,

00:49:33.810 --> 00:49:35.710 align:middle line:90%
would it weigh 1/3000th?

00:49:35.710 --> 00:49:37.280 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, you can't
weigh one of them.

00:49:37.280 --> 00:49:38.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Why?

00:49:38.080 --> 00:49:41.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Because it's one particle.

00:49:41.600 --> 00:49:45.320 align:middle line:84%
It's just-- It's is one
indivisible particle.

00:49:45.320 --> 00:49:48.230 align:middle line:90%
>> But if it's--

00:49:48.230 --> 00:49:51.200 align:middle line:84%
but if it's in
different locations,

00:49:51.200 --> 00:49:52.850 align:middle line:90%
can't you put a scale under one?

00:49:52.850 --> 00:49:55.880 align:middle line:90%
>> No, it's inseparable.

00:49:55.880 --> 00:49:59.300 align:middle line:84%
This is the tricky
conceptual part.

00:49:59.300 --> 00:50:03.310 align:middle line:90%
It's not 3,000 separate parts.

00:50:03.310 --> 00:50:04.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Even though it
looks that way?

00:50:04.780 --> 00:50:05.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:50:05.420 --> 00:50:06.200 align:middle line:90%
You can look at it.

00:50:06.200 --> 00:50:08.480 align:middle line:84%
And, I mean, you can't actually
see the one with 3,000.

00:50:08.480 --> 00:50:10.022 align:middle line:84%
But you can look at
the simpler ones,

00:50:10.022 --> 00:50:12.920 align:middle line:84%
the ones that are two or three
or four and you can see them.

00:50:12.920 --> 00:50:17.090 align:middle line:84%
You can see, as I say,
if you go onto the web,

00:50:17.090 --> 00:50:19.510 align:middle line:90%
you'll see photographs of these.

00:50:19.510 --> 00:50:22.610 align:middle line:84%
And you'll see these little
dots floating in space.

00:50:22.610 --> 00:50:26.600 align:middle line:84%
These are the different
parts of one object.

00:50:26.600 --> 00:50:30.470 align:middle line:90%
They're not separable.

00:50:30.470 --> 00:50:32.870 align:middle line:84%
It's not four different objects
or six different objects,

00:50:32.870 --> 00:50:36.410 align:middle line:84%
it's one wave function,
it's one object.

00:50:36.410 --> 00:50:38.360 align:middle line:84%
>> That's a real
brain fart, isn't it?

00:50:38.360 --> 00:50:41.030 align:middle line:84%
Because when you think about
it, wait a minute, no, no, no,

00:50:41.030 --> 00:50:43.300 align:middle line:84%
they're, like, here, here,
here, so it's obviously

00:50:43.300 --> 00:50:44.100 align:middle line:90%
one, two, three.

00:50:44.100 --> 00:50:46.760 align:middle line:84%
>> No, and you can't pull
one away from the others.

00:50:46.760 --> 00:50:48.740 align:middle line:84%
If you try to pull one
away from the others,

00:50:48.740 --> 00:50:51.548 align:middle line:84%
the entire thing
will just disappear.

00:50:51.548 --> 00:50:53.840 align:middle line:84%
And then furthermore, you
know, you've seen "Star Trek"

00:50:53.840 --> 00:50:55.810 align:middle line:84%
and whatnot, "Beam
me up, Scotty."

00:50:55.810 --> 00:50:56.810 align:middle line:90%
>> "Beam me up, Scotty."

00:50:56.810 --> 00:51:00.095 align:middle line:84%
>> So it all seems sort
of, oh, well, you know,

00:51:00.095 --> 00:51:01.220 align:middle line:90%
what does that really mean?

00:51:01.220 --> 00:51:02.960 align:middle line:84%
But you've got to
really stop and think

00:51:02.960 --> 00:51:05.600 align:middle line:84%
about what that means,
that it's the same object

00:51:05.600 --> 00:51:07.250 align:middle line:90%
and it's in two places at once.

00:51:07.250 --> 00:51:08.665 align:middle line:10%
And then people
tinker in the lab

00:51:08.665 --> 00:51:10.790 align:middle line:10%
and they get angry about
things and they have lunch

00:51:10.790 --> 00:51:13.250 align:middle line:10%
and they go home and they
lead their lives just as

00:51:13.250 --> 00:51:15.418 align:middle line:10%
though nothing utterly
astounding is happening.

00:51:15.418 --> 00:51:17.710 align:middle line:84%
Because, of course, that's
how you have to go about it.

00:51:17.710 --> 00:51:22.953 align:middle line:84%
And yet there is this completely
amazing magic sitting right

00:51:22.953 --> 00:51:23.870 align:middle line:90%
in front of your eyes.

00:51:23.870 --> 00:51:35.702 align:middle line:90%


00:51:35.702 --> 00:51:39.153 align:middle line:90%
[PHONE RINGING]

00:51:39.153 --> 00:51:46.560 align:middle line:90%


00:51:46.560 --> 00:51:47.960 align:middle line:90%
>> Where the hell are you?

00:51:47.960 --> 00:51:49.335 align:middle line:10%
I've got a studio
full of people,

00:51:49.335 --> 00:51:54.910 align:middle line:10%
but oh my god, there's
no photographer.

00:51:54.910 --> 00:51:55.742 align:middle line:90%
Where?

00:51:55.742 --> 00:51:57.436 align:middle line:90%
Where can she be?

00:51:57.436 --> 00:51:59.620 align:middle line:90%
Aliens?

00:51:59.620 --> 00:52:01.106 align:middle line:90%
Loch Ness Monster?

00:52:01.106 --> 00:52:02.280 align:middle line:90%
Or a hot date?

00:52:02.280 --> 00:52:04.830 align:middle line:90%


00:52:04.830 --> 00:52:08.850 align:middle line:84%
>> We took two simple
black boxes like this.

00:52:08.850 --> 00:52:11.220 align:middle line:10%
Inside is a very
simple electric circuit

00:52:11.220 --> 00:52:15.120 align:middle line:10%
with a few diodes,
an oscillator, EPROM,

00:52:15.120 --> 00:52:17.250 align:middle line:10%
some resistors and capacitors.

00:52:17.250 --> 00:52:19.470 align:middle line:90%
Basically, that's it.

00:52:19.470 --> 00:52:21.710 align:middle line:84%
We wrapped one in
aluminum foil, we

00:52:21.710 --> 00:52:24.800 align:middle line:84%
put it in an electrically
grounded Faraday cage.

00:52:24.800 --> 00:52:28.800 align:middle line:84%
The other we set on a
tabletop around which four,

00:52:28.800 --> 00:52:32.010 align:middle line:84%
very well qualified
meditators, highly inner self

00:52:32.010 --> 00:52:34.110 align:middle line:90%
managed individuals sit.

00:52:34.110 --> 00:52:38.670 align:middle line:84%
And they go into a
deep meditative state.

00:52:38.670 --> 00:52:41.310 align:middle line:90%
They cleanse the environment.

00:52:41.310 --> 00:52:43.740 align:middle line:84%
They make it, essentially,
a sacred space

00:52:43.740 --> 00:52:46.430 align:middle line:84%
using their mind
cleansing procedures

00:52:46.430 --> 00:52:48.010 align:middle line:90%
and their intentions.

00:52:48.010 --> 00:52:50.970 align:middle line:84%
And then one of the four
speaks the specific intention

00:52:50.970 --> 00:52:52.410 align:middle line:90%
for this device.

00:52:52.410 --> 00:52:56.601 align:middle line:84%
The intention is to influence
a particular target experiment.

00:52:56.601 --> 00:53:00.690 align:middle line:84%
It might be to increase the
pH of the purified water

00:53:00.690 --> 00:53:06.180 align:middle line:84%
by one full pH or to decrease
the pH by one full pH unit.

00:53:06.180 --> 00:53:08.940 align:middle line:84%
We've used these devices
on all those experiments

00:53:08.940 --> 00:53:11.010 align:middle line:84%
and have been
robustly successful.

00:53:11.010 --> 00:53:13.770 align:middle line:84%
In the meditative
process, then after one

00:53:13.770 --> 00:53:17.190 align:middle line:84%
speaks the particular
intention, it's

00:53:17.190 --> 00:53:22.290 align:middle line:84%
held various ways by the
four for maybe 15 minutes.

00:53:22.290 --> 00:53:25.980 align:middle line:90%
And then so be it, it's let go.

00:53:25.980 --> 00:53:27.760 align:middle line:84%
And then a subsidiary
intention is

00:53:27.760 --> 00:53:32.740 align:middle line:84%
stated to seal that
imprint into the device.

00:53:32.740 --> 00:53:37.060 align:middle line:84%
We take one of these devices
with its aluminum foil,

00:53:37.060 --> 00:53:38.770 align:middle line:90%
we put it in a soft package.

00:53:38.770 --> 00:53:40.660 align:middle line:90%
We put in a FedEx packet.

00:53:40.660 --> 00:53:43.320 align:middle line:84%
We ship it 2,000 miles
away to the laboratory

00:53:43.320 --> 00:53:46.330 align:middle line:90%
we're using up in Minnesota.

00:53:46.330 --> 00:53:49.900 align:middle line:84%
And soon as it arrives there it
goes into its own electrically

00:53:49.900 --> 00:53:51.460 align:middle line:90%
grounded Faraday cage.

00:53:51.460 --> 00:53:54.060 align:middle line:84%
The next day we do the
same with the control.

00:53:54.060 --> 00:53:57.190 align:middle line:84%
The experiment is running,
and basically then one

00:53:57.190 --> 00:53:59.170 align:middle line:84%
just takes the
device out, sets it

00:53:59.170 --> 00:54:01.960 align:middle line:84%
beside the experiment
within 6 inches to a foot,

00:54:01.960 --> 00:54:05.500 align:middle line:84%
and turns it on for a
period time, that's it.

00:54:05.500 --> 00:54:09.370 align:middle line:84%
Now, we learned over
some period of time

00:54:09.370 --> 00:54:10.720 align:middle line:90%
that there was another factor.

00:54:10.720 --> 00:54:15.640 align:middle line:84%
We found that the use of
these, we call them intention

00:54:15.640 --> 00:54:18.580 align:middle line:84%
imprinted electrical
devices, the continued use

00:54:18.580 --> 00:54:23.890 align:middle line:84%
of this somehow
conditions the space

00:54:23.890 --> 00:54:26.620 align:middle line:84%
to some higher
level of symmetry.

00:54:26.620 --> 00:54:29.950 align:middle line:84%
And we start getting
new phenomena,

00:54:29.950 --> 00:54:31.720 align:middle line:90%
that is, the devices work.

00:54:31.720 --> 00:54:34.660 align:middle line:84%
That is, the pH which
is normal starts

00:54:34.660 --> 00:54:38.500 align:middle line:84%
rising one full pH if
that was the imprint,

00:54:38.500 --> 00:54:40.990 align:middle line:90%
or it starts dropping.

00:54:40.990 --> 00:54:45.020 align:middle line:84%
If you go one full pH unit
or beyond, you're dead.

00:54:45.020 --> 00:54:48.710 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's what
it means to a human.

00:54:48.710 --> 00:54:52.390 align:middle line:84%
>> REG machines, random event
generators are electronic

00:54:52.390 --> 00:54:53.410 align:middle line:90%
tosses of the coin.

00:54:53.410 --> 00:54:55.750 align:middle line:84%
>> One type of random
number generator experiment

00:54:55.750 --> 00:54:58.120 align:middle line:84%
that's been conducted
many, many times,

00:54:58.120 --> 00:55:02.500 align:middle line:84%
hundreds of times over the past
four decades or so since around

00:55:02.500 --> 00:55:06.850 align:middle line:84%
the 1960s has been a random
generator that only produces

00:55:06.850 --> 00:55:12.100 align:middle line:84%
sequences of random bits, zeros
and ones, like flipping coins.

00:55:12.100 --> 00:55:14.790 align:middle line:84%
And you would simply ask
somebody to press a button,

00:55:14.790 --> 00:55:16.390 align:middle line:90%
it would produce 200 bits.

00:55:16.390 --> 00:55:17.890 align:middle line:84%
And you would ask
them to say, well,

00:55:17.890 --> 00:55:21.670 align:middle line:84%
try to make it produce more
one bit than zero bits.

00:55:21.670 --> 00:55:24.393 align:middle line:84%
And when you take the
entire body of literature,

00:55:24.393 --> 00:55:25.810 align:middle line:84%
all of the hundreds
of experiments

00:55:25.810 --> 00:55:28.690 align:middle line:84%
that have been done, you
can ask a single question,

00:55:28.690 --> 00:55:31.720 align:middle line:84%
did it matter that people were
trying to push it towards ones

00:55:31.720 --> 00:55:33.970 align:middle line:90%
or push it towards zeros?

00:55:33.970 --> 00:55:36.670 align:middle line:84%
And the overall answer
is, yes, it does matter,

00:55:36.670 --> 00:55:41.050 align:middle line:84%
that somehow intention is
correlated with the operation,

00:55:41.050 --> 00:55:44.080 align:middle line:84%
with the output of these
random number generators,

00:55:44.080 --> 00:55:46.870 align:middle line:84%
such that if you
wish for more ones,

00:55:46.870 --> 00:55:49.520 align:middle line:84%
somehow the generators
produce more ones.

00:55:49.520 --> 00:55:52.270 align:middle line:84%
>> So when they talk about
in quantum physics being

00:55:52.270 --> 00:55:55.570 align:middle line:84%
a completely arbitrary
and random process,

00:55:55.570 --> 00:56:00.220 align:middle line:84%
what they're not accounting
for is the extraordinary effect

00:56:00.220 --> 00:56:02.260 align:middle line:84%
of human thought,
of human intention.

00:56:02.260 --> 00:56:05.140 align:middle line:84%
>> When the OJ Simpson trial was
going on, a lot of people were

00:56:05.140 --> 00:56:08.170 align:middle line:84%
watching television because of
the courtroom drama that was

00:56:08.170 --> 00:56:09.100 align:middle line:90%
unfolding.

00:56:09.100 --> 00:56:12.550 align:middle line:84%
And Radin intuited
that there must

00:56:12.550 --> 00:56:15.310 align:middle line:84%
be a lot of intention
going on at the time

00:56:15.310 --> 00:56:17.440 align:middle line:84%
when the courtroom
drama is strong.

00:56:17.440 --> 00:56:19.990 align:middle line:84%
So he hired a bunch of
psychologists who kept

00:56:19.990 --> 00:56:22.210 align:middle line:90%
track of the courtroom drama.

00:56:22.210 --> 00:56:25.180 align:middle line:84%
At the same time, Radin
was studying the behavior

00:56:25.180 --> 00:56:27.670 align:middle line:90%
of random number generators.

00:56:27.670 --> 00:56:32.050 align:middle line:84%
But then Radin found that
whenever the intentions were

00:56:32.050 --> 00:56:34.960 align:middle line:84%
strong in the
courtroom, that's when

00:56:34.960 --> 00:56:39.230 align:middle line:84%
the deviation of
these random number

00:56:39.230 --> 00:56:44.240 align:middle line:84%
generators from randomness
becomes very high.

00:56:44.240 --> 00:56:48.410 align:middle line:84%
>> This leads naturally to
wonder are people affecting

00:56:48.410 --> 00:56:50.630 align:middle line:84%
the world of reality
that they see?

00:56:50.630 --> 00:56:52.580 align:middle line:90%
You betcha they are.

00:56:52.580 --> 00:56:56.240 align:middle line:84%
Every single one of us affects
the reality that we see.

00:56:56.240 --> 00:57:00.020 align:middle line:84%
Even if we try to hide
from that and play victim,

00:57:00.020 --> 00:57:01.970 align:middle line:90%
we all are doing it.

00:57:01.970 --> 00:57:04.820 align:middle line:90%


00:57:04.820 --> 00:57:08.460 align:middle line:90%
>> Just tell me where you are?

00:57:08.460 --> 00:57:09.260 align:middle line:90%
Good.

00:57:09.260 --> 00:57:10.480 align:middle line:84%
Well, just hurry,
will you, please?

00:57:10.480 --> 00:57:12.540 align:middle line:84%
Because these models are
giving me a headache.

